			<p>I would like to thank Krista Bremer for her essay &ldquo;<a href="/article/338">Driven by Desire</a>&rdquo; [June 2005]. Like her husband, I have a special bond with my 1986 Toyota Tercel. While Bremer yearned for power windows, my five-year-old daughter believes the hand-crank windows in my Tercel are magic &mdash; because they go up or down even when the engine is off!</p>
							<p class="quote-2-author">Chris Osterbauer<br>Ellsworth, Maine</p>
